course.subject: OCES
course.name: Data Analysis in Ocean Science
course.description: The goal of the course is to learn basic numerical analysis tools needed to compute and practice simple techniques for analyzing oceanographic data. These analysis include basic statistics, curve fitting, and simple graphics. Students will learn these techniques through examples from ocean data sets. Students will learn to conduct these analyses with Python or R and are not assumed to have experience in programming.
course.prerequisites: (MATH 2411 OR LIFS 3150 OR DASC 2220) AND (COMP 1021 OR COMP 1029P)
